WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:45.211 --> 00:47.589
<i>Historically,
when we look at evolution...</i>

00:47.756 --> 00:50.759
<i>...it's not surprising
that Chappie's left turn happened.</i>

00:52.802 --> 00:57.390
<i>It's too early to tell how
this is all going to play out.</i>

00:57.557 --> 00:59.957
<i>I didn't believe this would happen
in my lifetime, but it is.</i>

01:05.522 --> 01:07.025
<i>Downtown Johannesburg.</i>

01:07.192 --> 01:08.526
<i>It's a dangerous city.</i>

01:08.693 --> 01:13.406
<i>Each day, more than 300 murders
and violent attacks take place here.</i>

01:16.534 --> 01:19.704
<i>Two officers have been killed,
three taken to the hospital.</i>

01:19.871 --> 01:23.166
<i>A bloody end to a shoot-out
between cops and robbers.</i>

01:23.333 --> 01:25.627
<i>Another man in blue dead.</i>

01:27.754 --> 01:31.883
Today, we usher in a new day.

01:32.050 --> 01:36.596
<i>- One that represents the end of crime.
- Move in. Lock on target. Fire! Fire!</i>

01:37.138 --> 01:39.099
The end of corruption.

01:39.849 --> 01:42.143
<i>Go! Go! Up against the wall!</i>

01:42.310 --> 01:43.853
<i>On the ground.</i>

01:44.020 --> 01:46.648
<i>- All targets neutralized.
- And the start...</i>

01:46.815 --> 01:49.609
...of the rebirth of our city!

01:51.528 --> 01:55.365
<i>Welcome to the world's
first robotic police force.</i>

02:07.460 --> 02:11.631
<i>Johannesburg, South Africa, became
the focus of the world in 2016...</i>

02:11.798 --> 02:15.468
<i>...with the deployment of the planet's
first all-robotic police units.</i>

02:16.803 --> 02:20.974
<i>Crime levels plummeted,
and Tetravaal stock skyrocketed.</i>

02:22.308 --> 02:26.354
<i>Certain parts are from China, but all robots
are assembled right here in South Africa.</i>

02:26.521 --> 02:30.483
<i>The population's biggest fear
was vulnerability to hacking.</i>

02:30.650 --> 02:33.653
<i>Tetravaal assures this is not
something to worry about...</i>

02:33.820 --> 02:36.072
<i>...with their bulletproof
Guard Key system.</i>

02:36.239 --> 02:40.535
<i>A system which allows only them
to update software on the robots.</i>

02:41.244 --> 02:44.748
<i>Before the success of the ubiquitous
human-sized police robots...</i>

02:44.914 --> 02:48.001
<i>...there was a bigger bad boy
on the block: the Moose.</i>

02:48.168 --> 02:51.713
<i>Vincent Moore is a weapons designer
and a former soldier.</i>

02:51.880 --> 02:55.175
<i>He has a spiritual issue
with artificial intelligence.</i>

02:55.342 --> 02:57.135
<i>I have a robot that is indestructible.</i>

02:58.553 --> 03:01.639
<i>It is operated
by a thinking, adaptable...</i>

03:01.806 --> 03:04.726
<i>...humane, moral human being.</i>

03:04.893 --> 03:07.354
<i>The advanced neural transmitter
converts...</i>

03:07.520 --> 03:10.648
<i>...the human operator's thoughts
into the robot's actions.</i>

03:10.815 --> 03:14.110
<i>A departure from the AI
that governs the Scouts.</i>

03:14.277 --> 03:17.364
<i>Now with interest from the U.S.,
China and North Korea...</i>

03:17.530 --> 03:20.742
<i>...the Scouts' creator, Deon Wilson,
sees a rich future.</i>

03:20.909 --> 03:22.952
<i>What really interests me
is high-level AI.</i>

03:24.329 --> 03:28.208
<i>True intelligence.
A machine that can think and feel.</i>

03:28.375 --> 03:30.627
<i>Is that the mandate at Tetravaal?</i>

03:30.794 --> 03:35.674
<i>To take that evolutionary step forward
and build something truly alive?</i>

03:41.554 --> 03:44.182
<i>Scout 22 arriving now
at Maintenance Bay 6.</i>

03:44.349 --> 03:46.601
- Team 1, off deck. Go!
- Hurry. Open it up.

03:46.768 --> 03:48.978
- Let's get him out.
- Load it up!

03:49.145 --> 03:50.980
- He's pretty banged up.
- Oh, my God.

03:51.147 --> 03:53.024
- Come on!
- Ready to go.

03:58.905 --> 04:01.074
Oh, chrissakes.

04:01.825 --> 04:03.868
See this 22? Luck of the draw.

04:04.035 --> 04:05.704
They used him as a speed bump.

04:05.870 --> 04:08.790
Look at this.
It's like he's cursed or something.

04:08.957 --> 04:11.835
Every time he goes out.
Now, yeah, it's his ear.

04:12.002 --> 04:14.087
Antenna, right.
Can we switch this out?

04:14.254 --> 04:15.630
Check that circuit again.

04:16.589 --> 04:18.800
Terminal on 7 and 7A.

04:23.972 --> 04:27.600
<i>Reports of gunfire
in Sections 5, 7 and 8.</i>

04:27.767 --> 04:28.768
Okay, fire it up.

04:28.935 --> 04:31.980
<i>Police request all available Scouts
to be mobilized.</i>

04:40.155 --> 04:42.073
Destination or task.

04:42.240 --> 04:43.950
Helipad. Yeah?

04:47.829 --> 04:50.582
Hey, 22, just watch yourself
this time, eh?

04:50.749 --> 04:52.375
Affirmative.

05:03.011 --> 05:05.638
- We're in shit!
- Duh, we in shit, Amerika!

05:05.805 --> 05:07.140
I said it was a bad deal.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.851
- I said it over and over.
- Everybody, just chill!

05:10.018 --> 05:12.937
Yes, we have a problem.
And, yes, I'm gonna solve it!

05:13.730 --> 05:16.983
<i>Command, we are searching
for suspects driving a gray vehicle.</i>

05:21.863 --> 05:23.907
Hey. They're here!

05:33.958 --> 05:36.211
- What's up with this shit?
- Looks pissed.

05:39.422 --> 05:41.257
Hippo.

05:42.634 --> 05:44.219
Listen, some shit went down.

05:44.386 --> 05:45.553
Wasn't our fault.

05:46.429 --> 05:47.430
Your weapon.

05:48.098 --> 05:49.724
Fuck's sakes.

05:49.891 --> 05:50.892
And your keys.

05:52.268 --> 05:53.269
Come on.

05:53.436 --> 05:54.646
Open the back.

05:57.649 --> 05:59.776
Hey, hey, hey!

06:05.699 --> 06:07.992
We're lucky to be alive, Hippo.

06:09.619 --> 06:10.620
Ninja.

06:11.996 --> 06:14.541
You know there's no way out of this.

06:14.708 --> 06:17.711
There's always a way.
Name your price. We'll sort you out.

06:17.877 --> 06:19.671
My price?

06:20.088 --> 06:21.172
Is 20 million.

06:21.339 --> 06:23.967
- Come on, man. Ridiculous.
- What the fuck?

06:24.134 --> 06:25.677
Fuck I'm gonna pay that back, dude?

06:25.844 --> 06:27.262
Get on your knees.

06:27.429 --> 06:30.765
- Now, get on your fucking knees!
- Okay, okay, okay.

06:32.308 --> 06:34.060
You owe me...

06:34.602 --> 06:36.563
...20 million. Say it.

06:36.730 --> 06:38.231
I owe you 20 million.

06:42.652 --> 06:44.904
- Pitbull. Pitbull!
- Get back!

06:45.071 --> 06:47.032
- Get back!
- Jesus Christ, Hippo.

06:47.198 --> 06:48.783
Seven days.

06:48.950 --> 06:50.702
You've got seven days.

06:51.161 --> 06:53.580
Droids! Droids!

06:54.122 --> 06:55.540
You were followed!

06:57.459 --> 07:00.086
- Get behind the wall!
- Yo-Landi, get in the van.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.254
- Let's go!
- Get in!

07:01.421 --> 07:03.089
Hit the explosives!

07:05.759 --> 07:08.845
- They detonated some explosive.
- Shit! Droids!

07:09.012 --> 07:10.972
Can't get a clear shot.
Touching down.

07:11.139 --> 07:12.724
Moving out.

07:18.480 --> 07:21.358
- Who took the keys?
- You gave it to that guy!

07:21.524 --> 07:23.568
Human officers are on the ground.

07:23.735 --> 07:25.236
Let's go! Let's move!

07:31.743 --> 07:33.203
Move out!

07:35.330 --> 07:37.999
Move out, 22. Go, go, go!

07:38.166 --> 07:41.252
Drop your weapons.
You are under arrest.

07:44.714 --> 07:46.466
Break right! Go, go, go!

07:48.259 --> 07:50.970
Come on. Where are the keys?

07:51.137 --> 07:52.222
Cue, on my left!

07:52.389 --> 07:55.308
- Kill these cops!
- Move! Get back!

08:01.147 --> 08:02.816
Yes, yes.

08:02.982 --> 08:04.109
Drop your weapons.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.070
Go!

08:08.655 --> 08:11.116
Hey, <i>poes!</i> I need my keys, please!

08:12.075 --> 08:13.410
Fuck you!

08:15.495 --> 08:18.331
- Drop your weapon. Drop your weapon!
- Fuck you!

08:25.880 --> 08:27.132
Come on.

08:29.009 --> 08:30.010
For sure, <i>baas</i>.

08:42.188 --> 08:44.691
Shit! They hit the rotor.
We need to touch down.

08:47.944 --> 08:49.696
Thank you very much.

08:50.238 --> 08:52.532
Twenty-two, going in.

09:13.928 --> 09:15.138
Droid 22 is down, sir.

09:16.514 --> 09:18.099
Bravo 1! We need backup!

09:18.266 --> 09:20.435
<i>Copy that. We're sending droids.</i>

09:21.478 --> 09:24.397
- Amerika! Amerika! I've got the keys!
- Your keys.

09:24.564 --> 09:26.941
- Hey, Landi, he's got the keys!
- Let's go!

09:30.737 --> 09:33.198
Get out of the vehicle.

09:33.365 --> 09:34.491
Go!

09:37.327 --> 09:39.245
Do not run.

09:43.041 --> 09:46.002
- Are you okay?
- I'm not okay! I'm hit!

09:52.008 --> 09:54.552
<i>Scout 22 is non-responsive.</i>

09:54.719 --> 09:56.179
<i>Send an evac team.</i>

09:56.846 --> 09:59.432
<i>Yet another victory
for the robotic police force.</i>

09:59.599 --> 10:03.311
<i>This marks the 30th large-scale
crime ring smashed this year.</i>

10:03.812 --> 10:05.689
- Good morning, Deon.
- Good morning.

10:07.190 --> 10:08.566
People...

10:08.733 --> 10:11.069
...if I may have your attention, please.

10:11.444 --> 10:13.363
<i>The police chief just called me...</i>

10:13.530 --> 10:16.950
<i>...to place an order
for another 100 Scouts.</i>

10:17.117 --> 10:19.202
This is very, very good news.

10:20.245 --> 10:21.287
Way to go!

10:21.454 --> 10:23.456
- Deon.
- Nice job!

10:23.623 --> 10:25.083
Well done, dude. Well done.

10:25.250 --> 10:26.751
- Congrats, D.
- Thank you, man.

10:26.918 --> 10:28.586
- Well done, Deon.
- Great.

10:28.753 --> 10:30.922
- Congratulations.
- Thanks. Thank you.

10:31.089 --> 10:32.882
- I appreciate it.
- Nice job, buddy.

10:33.049 --> 10:35.552
- I couldn't have done it without you.
- I know.

10:36.511 --> 10:39.472
- Congrats, man. You're awesome.
- Nice job, mate!

10:44.811 --> 10:47.188
Is this the "I feel sorry
for Vincent" call?

10:47.355 --> 10:49.482
- Don't worry, Vince.
<i>- Well, I am worried.</i>

10:49.649 --> 10:50.692
Well, look...

10:50.859 --> 10:52.986
<i>...we have one more stab
with the police.</i>

10:53.153 --> 10:54.904
<i>Try to get those costs down.</i>

10:55.071 --> 10:57.157
Try to think positive, okay?

10:57.323 --> 10:58.950
- Chin up.
- <i>Kind of hard...</i>

10:59.117 --> 11:03.329
...when you keep cutting my funding.
Twenty percent this year, 25 last year.

11:03.496 --> 11:05.540
I've got work to do on the Moose.

11:05.707 --> 11:08.460
The threat detection is still
in its elemental phase.

11:08.626 --> 11:12.547
<i>Threat detection is superfluous.
The operator detects the threat.</i>

11:12.714 --> 11:14.341
<i>Then we send the Moose out.</i>

11:14.507 --> 11:16.301
Enough already.

11:17.177 --> 11:19.262
Cut. Not add.

11:19.429 --> 11:22.223
<i>- Okay?</i>
- Yeah. I'm on it.

11:22.724 --> 11:26.644
<i>- Deon Wilson to the workshop.</i>
- I need to go. I'll talk to you in a bit.

11:34.986 --> 11:36.821
It's my little boy in again, eh?

11:36.988 --> 11:40.241
Fucking surprise, surprise.
Every time. He's a bullet magnet.

11:40.408 --> 11:43.870
- What's going on, guys?
- Here's the report. It's 22. Again.

11:44.037 --> 11:45.789
RPG, direct to the chest.

11:45.955 --> 11:48.333
See a lot of the internals got damaged.

11:48.917 --> 11:52.545
- Brain architecture's still intact.
- Regardless, it's a write-off.

11:52.712 --> 11:56.216
- Okay, let's salvage the CPU.
- We could try to cut the battery out.

11:56.383 --> 11:59.719
- It's still charged, still stable.
- No, not worth the effort.

11:59.886 --> 12:03.598
Droid 22 written off. Crush the chassis
and recycle the alloys. Yeah?

12:03.765 --> 12:05.266
- Sure.
- Thank you.

12:13.400 --> 12:14.901
Easy, easy, easy.

12:15.068 --> 12:17.278
Come, come, come. Into the lair.

12:17.445 --> 12:19.823
- Careful, man.
- We need to stitch his shit up.

12:30.917 --> 12:32.293
You think you got away?

12:32.460 --> 12:34.337
No, I didn't think that, Hippo.

12:34.504 --> 12:36.589
You think you don't owe me
this money anymore?

12:36.756 --> 12:38.633
<i>Because you think
I'm in prison or what?</i>

12:38.800 --> 12:39.968
We'll get your money.

12:40.135 --> 12:42.512
Maybe I come to your secret place
in Soweto.

12:43.054 --> 12:45.306
<i>I come there with the fellows.</i>

12:45.473 --> 12:46.933
I take what I want.

12:47.100 --> 12:48.643
It's cool. One week.

12:48.810 --> 12:50.228
Seven days!

12:54.149 --> 12:56.192
- They didn't catch that <i>poes</i>.
- What?

12:56.359 --> 12:57.819
He knows where we live.

12:57.986 --> 13:00.071
We got a week to come up
with his money.

13:00.238 --> 13:03.033
How are we gonna do that?
Come on, that's ridiculous.

13:03.199 --> 13:05.702
We need one final job.

13:05.869 --> 13:09.581
I'm talking about serious cash.

13:09.748 --> 13:11.833
Five hundred million rand. Okay?

13:12.542 --> 13:15.211
We pay that animal.
We pocket the rest.

13:15.378 --> 13:18.381
And we get out
while we still can. Boom.

13:18.548 --> 13:20.717
What are you getting on about,
a bank job?

13:20.884 --> 13:22.052
No.

13:22.552 --> 13:24.012
- Cash in transit.
- What?

13:24.179 --> 13:26.056
- That's what?
- A heist, Yo-Landi.

13:26.222 --> 13:28.808
The droids are gonna come down
on our asses, okay?

13:28.975 --> 13:30.769
- They'll hit us harder.
- It's true.

13:30.935 --> 13:33.521
Guys, we need, like, a remote.

13:33.688 --> 13:35.982
- Like a switch.
- What? Excuse me?

13:36.524 --> 13:40.070
Okay, the robots are
like machines, right?

13:40.236 --> 13:41.321
Like a TV.

13:41.488 --> 13:44.532
So if we had a remote
to switch it off....

13:44.699 --> 13:46.034
That's brilliant.

13:46.201 --> 13:51.414
We need to find the guy who makes
the robots and steal his remotes.

14:01.299 --> 14:02.300
Dexter?

14:02.467 --> 14:05.136
Hello, Deon. Welcome home.

14:05.804 --> 14:08.181
- Have you been a good boy today?
- Yes, Deon.

14:08.348 --> 14:11.810
- Yeah? Did you clean my room?
- Your room has been sterilized.

14:11.976 --> 14:13.395
Nice.

14:13.812 --> 14:17.899
Are you working on your artificial
intelligence program tonight?

14:18.066 --> 14:20.527
- Yes.
- I will activate the kettle.

14:24.739 --> 14:26.074
<i>Okay.</i>

14:26.241 --> 14:27.409
<i>Hello again.</i>

14:27.575 --> 14:30.412
<i>So it's day 944.</i>

14:30.578 --> 14:32.497
<i>I'm extremely close now.</i>

14:32.664 --> 14:35.291
<i>There's always chance of error,
I'm aware of this.</i>

14:35.458 --> 14:39.254
<i>But statistically speaking,
I think I might be on track.</i>

14:39.421 --> 14:42.424
<i>I have several terabytes
of compiling and coding to do...</i>

14:42.590 --> 14:44.342
<i>...and then we shall see.</i>

14:44.509 --> 14:46.511
<i>All right? See you in a bit.</i>

14:52.642 --> 14:54.769
- Look. That's the motherfucker.
- Him?

14:56.896 --> 14:59.190
Dude, it's gonna be so easy.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.569
We need those remotes, my man.

15:03.111 --> 15:05.238
We need those remotes.

15:07.615 --> 15:08.742
Red Bull!

15:08.908 --> 15:10.243
Yes, Deon.

15:11.202 --> 15:12.662
Red Bull.

15:17.459 --> 15:18.793
Okay.

15:39.522 --> 15:40.899
Come on.

15:43.234 --> 15:44.861
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

15:45.820 --> 15:47.238
What if you change the...?

16:14.182 --> 16:16.726
- It's stable.
- Is everything okay?

16:19.896 --> 16:21.022
It's stable.

16:22.273 --> 16:23.608
<i>My God.</i>

16:23.775 --> 16:25.318
<i>I think I've cracked it.</i>

16:25.485 --> 16:28.988
<i>Of course, to really know,
I must test it on a live system.</i>

16:29.906 --> 16:31.491
<i>I must test it.</i>

16:40.291 --> 16:41.584
All right.

16:42.669 --> 16:44.462
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

16:46.631 --> 16:48.675
Hey. Hey!

16:48.842 --> 16:51.219
- Hey. Where's the Scout?
- How's it, sir? What?

16:51.386 --> 16:55.473
- The Scout, man, 22 for demolition.
- Guys are prepping the compactor.

16:55.640 --> 16:57.767
- It goes in soon.
- Oh, thank God.

16:59.102 --> 17:01.438
- Don't destroy it yet, okay?
- <i>Ja</i>, sure.

17:01.604 --> 17:04.107
Just wait for me,
but don't destroy it, okay?

17:05.775 --> 17:08.819
- Hello, ma'am.
- Morning, Deon.

17:09.570 --> 17:11.489
All right. Let's have it.

17:11.656 --> 17:15.577
- What are you proposing now?
- Ma'am, I think I've cracked it.

17:15.743 --> 17:19.204
The world's first proper,
full artificial intelligence.

17:19.372 --> 17:22.625
This is a computer system
that might be smarter than a human.

17:22.791 --> 17:24.711
I could show it a piece of art...

17:24.877 --> 17:28.757
...and this thing, this being,
could judge that art.

17:28.923 --> 17:32.260
It could decide if it liked it.

17:32.427 --> 17:34.846
It could write music and poetry.

17:35.013 --> 17:36.514
Okay. Stop.

17:36.681 --> 17:38.141
Please, Deon.

17:38.725 --> 17:40.602
Do you realize you just came...

17:40.769 --> 17:43.897
...to the CEO of a publicly traded
weapons corporation...

17:44.064 --> 17:46.900
...and pitched a robot
that can write poems?

17:47.067 --> 17:49.152
Well, if you just let me explain...

17:49.319 --> 17:53.031
Deon, Tetravaal is very happy
with you.

17:53.198 --> 17:55.325
The Scouts are a huge success.

17:55.492 --> 17:58.328
Ma'am, look,
it won't cost you anything.

17:58.495 --> 18:02.040
A droid downstairs was written off
yesterday, smashed beyond repair.

18:02.207 --> 18:04.292
Let me install this on it.

18:04.459 --> 18:07.671
- Please just let me test it.
- No. No, I'm sorry, Deon.

18:07.837 --> 18:10.173
You know
how insurance works for those...

18:10.340 --> 18:12.801
...all the red tape and the paperwork.

18:12.967 --> 18:14.844
Thank you for your time.

18:23.144 --> 18:27.440
<i>All new employees, please report
to Human Resources for orientation.</i>

18:32.237 --> 18:33.530
Shit.

18:34.656 --> 18:35.657
Hey, Bill.

18:55.218 --> 18:56.970
<i>Attention. Attention.</i>

18:57.137 --> 19:00.640
<i>Remember to have your security pass
visible at all times.</i>

19:02.058 --> 19:04.686
Hey. Can you give me
a hand over here?

19:34.341 --> 19:35.967
Come on. Come on.

19:38.636 --> 19:39.721
Come on.

19:47.562 --> 19:48.813
Thank you.

19:53.193 --> 19:55.362
Yep. Showtime.

20:08.541 --> 20:11.086
- What's up, homes?
- Hey. Hey, hey, hey!

20:13.797 --> 20:16.049
Please! Hey, what is it?

20:16.216 --> 20:18.593
This is you getting hijacked, my friend.

20:18.760 --> 20:20.011
Welcome to Joburg.

20:23.306 --> 20:26.810
And these are all part
of what makes the Moose unique...

20:26.976 --> 20:29.270
...and perfect for you
at the department.

20:29.437 --> 20:32.565
The strategic ability to neutralize
the enemy's targets.

20:32.732 --> 20:35.527
High-value targets:
radar installations...

20:35.694 --> 20:37.821
...aircraft, fuel storage locations.

20:37.987 --> 20:39.906
- Aircraft?
- Yes, sir.

20:41.366 --> 20:43.535
We're taking out an enemy's aircraft?

20:43.702 --> 20:45.829
We are talking
about urban crimes here?

